<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-26T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/412: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-26T13:00:00-05:00">January 26, 1934—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4. Under authorization of the President please extend on behalf of the
                            United States a formal and cordial recognition to the Government of El
                                Salvador.<note n="35" xml:id="d257fn35">The Chargé extended
                                recognition late in the afternoon of January 26, in a note which he
                                delivered personally to the Minister of Foreign Affairs
                                (816.01/425).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>